1
00:02:04,313 --> 00:02:05,940
Happy New Year, Jay.

2
00:02:35,742 --> 00:02:37,530
I feel like I’m going crazy.

3
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,597
Or am I already crazy?

4
00:02:44,376 --> 00:02:47,629
So much has happened ever since
I wore this uniform.

5
00:03:14,961 --> 00:03:17,214
Section E!!!

6
00:03:55,739 --> 00:03:57,574
Why did you even do that, Jay-jay?

7
00:03:57,741 --> 00:03:59,492
You almost got carried away!

8
00:04:00,577 --> 00:04:01,553
You really are crazy!

9
00:04:01,578 --> 00:04:02,679
You’re weak!

10
00:04:22,557 --> 00:04:24,851
Later I’m going to
see the King of Assholes,

11
00:04:25,268 --> 00:04:26,853
and after that…

12
00:04:41,326 --> 00:04:43,036
I already accepted Yuri’s proposal,

13
00:04:43,453 --> 00:04:45,830
so I shouldn’t have done that to Keifer.

14
00:04:46,247 --> 00:04:47,749
Control yourself, Jay.

15
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:49,167
Jay?

16
00:04:50,085 --> 00:04:51,086
Yes?

17
00:04:53,392 --> 00:04:54,393
Wow!

18
00:04:54,839 --> 00:04:56,883
Jay, the room looks so nice.

19
00:04:56,883 --> 00:04:59,179
Is this part of your New Year's resolution?

20
00:05:00,055 --> 00:05:03,684
Yes, Auntie.
A new look for a new life.

21
00:05:06,328 --> 00:05:08,578
By the way,
Yuri asked for permission.

22
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:11,645
He said he'll pick you up,
he's probably downstairs already.

23
00:05:11,815 --> 00:05:14,334
Ah okay, I'll go down in a while.

24
00:05:14,359 --> 00:05:15,359
Alright.

25
00:05:22,117 --> 00:05:23,660
Yuri…

26
00:05:23,910 --> 00:05:25,203
Right.

27
00:05:25,453 --> 00:05:28,665
I’m already engaged, so I shouldn’t be
thinking about Keifer anymore.

28
00:05:38,537 --> 00:05:39,812
You can do this, Jay-jay.

29
00:05:44,097 --> 00:05:46,391
Let’s just forget
what happened on New Year’s.

30
00:07:36,501 --> 00:07:37,502
Good morning.

31
00:07:39,295 --> 00:07:41,131
Give that to me, I’ll carry it.

32
00:07:42,048 --> 00:07:44,342
No, it’s fine.
It's not heavy.

33
00:07:47,345 --> 00:07:50,682
Why did you pick me up?
I can bike on my own.

34
00:07:52,014 --> 00:07:54,099
Of course—fiancé duties.

35
00:07:54,853 --> 00:07:56,312
Fiancé…

36
00:07:56,896 --> 00:07:59,190
Shit, it sounds so heavy.

37
00:07:59,271 --> 00:08:00,355
I’m not used to it.

38
00:08:02,944 --> 00:08:03,945
Let’s go.

39
00:08:04,571 --> 00:08:05,581
No.

40
00:08:06,447 --> 00:08:07,907
She’s not going with you.

41
00:08:08,158 --> 00:08:09,033
Leave.

42
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:10,743
You're not the one
who's going to decide here.

43
00:08:11,369 --> 00:08:15,331
Aries, it’s okay.
I also want to talk to Yuri.

44
00:08:15,707 --> 00:08:18,710
If you had just listened to me,

45
00:08:18,971 --> 00:08:21,473
you wouldn’t have been
set up in that engagement.

46
00:08:21,588 --> 00:08:22,564
Right?

47
00:08:22,589 --> 00:08:23,965
Engagement...

48
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:25,383
Set-up...

49
00:08:25,383 --> 00:08:26,384
Let's go.

50
00:08:58,507 --> 00:08:59,589
Are you okay?

51
00:08:59,614 --> 00:09:01,116
You’ve been quiet.

52
00:09:02,686 --> 00:09:04,526
Of course, I’m fine.

53
00:09:05,048 --> 00:09:06,841
Have you talked to Angelo yet?

54
00:09:08,977 --> 00:09:11,771
I'm not ready to talk to him yet.

55
00:09:16,935 --> 00:09:17,936
I'm sorry, Jay.

56
00:09:18,478 --> 00:09:20,823
I wasn’t honest about
my feelings for you.

57
00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:24,847
But from now on,
I’ll be more honest.

58
00:09:26,903 --> 00:09:28,321
We’re engaged.

59
00:09:28,803 --> 00:09:32,306
So I should also be honest with him
about what happened on New Year’s.

60
00:09:32,893 --> 00:09:34,394
Uhmm, I need to confess something—

61
00:09:34,419 --> 00:09:36,379
Is it about Keifer?

62
00:09:38,548 --> 00:09:39,549
It's okay, Jay.

63
00:09:41,885 --> 00:09:43,261
I don’t want to hear it anymore.

64
00:09:45,639 --> 00:09:46,640
I'm sorry.

65
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:48,391
You don’t need to apologize.

66
00:09:48,975 --> 00:09:50,435
I understand you,

67
00:09:51,154 --> 00:09:53,698
but I’ll wait for you Jay
no matter how long.

68
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,610
Even until the day of our wedding.

69
00:09:57,109 --> 00:09:58,568
If that's what it takes.

70
00:09:58,593 --> 00:09:59,594
Yuri.

71
00:10:05,242 --> 00:10:06,368
I'm okay, Jay.

72
00:10:07,494 --> 00:10:08,620
Don't worry.

73
00:10:10,595 --> 00:10:14,000
My only wish is that
you give me a chance.

74
00:10:14,584 --> 00:10:16,336
Please don't close off your heart.

75
00:10:17,212 --> 00:10:19,131
I hope you still choose me in the end.

76
00:10:27,055 --> 00:10:28,265
Honestly,

77
00:10:28,723 --> 00:10:31,226
I don’t even know what I feel for Yuri.

78
00:10:31,686 --> 00:10:33,021
Is it guilt?

79
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:34,855
Because he’s kind to me?

80
00:10:35,442 --> 00:10:38,070
Or is it because of
my obligation to my family?

81
00:10:38,650 --> 00:10:40,736
Ugh, whatever.
Whatever happens, happens.

82
00:10:42,737 --> 00:10:43,738
Uhm...

83
00:10:45,157 --> 00:10:48,201
How are we going to
tell our classmates?

84
00:10:48,702 --> 00:10:50,662
I don’t think they need to know.

85
00:10:51,329 --> 00:10:52,408
Why?

86
00:10:52,455 --> 00:10:54,082
It’ll just cause chaos if they find out—

87
00:10:54,082 --> 00:10:56,751
especially since they know
Keifer has feelings for you.

88
00:10:58,128 --> 00:11:01,840
Yeah, you’re right.
It might cause trouble.

89
00:11:16,771 --> 00:11:18,106
Great idea.

90
00:11:21,026 --> 00:11:22,152
There.

91
00:11:23,028 --> 00:11:24,446
That’s good.

92
00:11:27,465 --> 00:11:28,550
Ouch!

93
00:11:28,575 --> 00:11:29,784
What was that for?

94
00:11:31,578 --> 00:11:33,642
I don’t want things
to be awkward between us, Jay.

95
00:11:33,830 --> 00:11:36,374
Act like the same Jay you are
whenever we’re together,

96
00:11:36,374 --> 00:11:37,584
and I'll do the same.

97
00:11:39,085 --> 00:11:40,173
You’re right.

98
00:11:40,503 --> 00:11:42,047
Ouch! That really hurts!

99
00:11:42,839 --> 00:11:44,923
That’s not enough—
want one on your forehead too?

100
00:11:45,383 --> 00:11:47,135
Come on, let’s go.
We might be late.

101
00:11:47,184 --> 00:11:48,194
Wait, wait, wait.

102
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:48,970
- What?
- I forgot something.

103
00:11:48,970 --> 00:11:49,931
What?

104
00:11:56,853 --> 00:11:57,938
I'll go ahead.

105
00:12:00,398 --> 00:12:01,900
Can I ask for one more favor?

106
00:12:03,026 --> 00:12:04,056
What?

107
00:12:04,361 --> 00:12:06,196
Can you stop picking me up
and taking me home?

108
00:12:06,613 --> 00:12:10,200
Someone might,
you know, notice.

109
00:12:11,409 --> 00:12:12,410
Okay.

110
00:12:12,744 --> 00:12:13,745
Alright.

111
00:12:44,192 --> 00:12:46,569
Okay, Jay-jay.
We'll do what is right.

112
00:12:46,669 --> 00:12:49,339
You're already engaged to Yuri,
time to forget about Keif—

113
00:12:49,364 --> 00:12:50,369
Fuck!

114
00:12:53,034 --> 00:12:55,745
Tss. Profanity on
the first day back?

115
00:12:56,538 --> 00:12:58,290
Or did you just miss my lips?

116
00:12:59,582 --> 00:13:00,875
What? Keifer!

117
00:13:01,793 --> 00:13:03,628
- Stop this.
- Why?

118
00:13:03,795 --> 00:13:06,381
- What do you mean "why"? Keifer, please.
- Stop what?

119
00:13:07,132 --> 00:13:11,303
This! What you're doing right now.
Stop flirting with me.

120
00:13:12,178 --> 00:13:15,348
What's wrong if I flirt with you?

121
00:13:16,891 --> 00:13:19,185
What's wrong if I flirt
with the one I love?

122
00:13:22,647 --> 00:13:24,232
It's wrong.

123
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:26,985
It's as if I'm cheating on Yuri.

124
00:13:27,861 --> 00:13:29,181
We're already engaged,

125
00:13:29,237 --> 00:13:30,322
stay away from me.

126
00:13:32,073 --> 00:13:33,283
Cheating?

127
00:13:34,132 --> 00:13:36,050
We're not in a relationship.

128
00:13:36,578 --> 00:13:38,371
So how are we cheating on him?

129
00:13:38,997 --> 00:13:40,957
You're not cheating on Yuri

130
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:43,793
because we're not in a relationship.

131
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:53,219
If that's the case,
then leave me alone!

132
00:13:55,055 --> 00:13:58,683
We're not in a relationship, but…

133
00:14:01,019 --> 00:14:02,354
you are mine.

134
00:14:02,937 --> 00:14:04,898
You know what, you're crazy.

135
00:14:05,815 --> 00:14:07,108
Crazy for you?

136
00:14:07,108 --> 00:14:08,777
Yeah, I think so.

137
00:14:39,432 --> 00:14:41,726
I’ll wait for you Jay no matter how long.

138
00:14:41,726 --> 00:14:43,353
Even until the day of our wedding.

139
00:14:48,274 --> 00:14:49,359
Fuck!

140
00:14:55,365 --> 00:14:56,741
You'll pay for this!

141
00:15:06,209 --> 00:15:08,920
Welcome back, bro!

142
00:15:09,838 --> 00:15:11,297
Come on, hurry, let’s play.

143
00:15:14,509 --> 00:15:15,218
Jay!

144
00:15:15,218 --> 00:15:16,302
How was vacation?

145
00:15:16,970 --> 00:15:18,596
It was okay.
How about you and Mica?

146
00:15:19,222 --> 00:15:20,598
Obviously they ran out of condoms again—

147
00:15:20,598 --> 00:15:22,267
he even asked me for some.
Said it wasn’t enough.

148
00:15:22,267 --> 00:15:23,643
- He asked you?
- Idiot!

149
00:15:24,727 --> 00:15:25,270
Asshole!

150
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:26,354
Unbelievable!

151
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:28,982
- Ouch!
- Hey, Jay!

152
00:15:29,149 --> 00:15:31,067
Everyone already went on vacation
but you're still sour.

153
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:32,068
Didn't you—

154
00:15:32,277 --> 00:15:34,487
Stop it!
It’s New Year, have you changed?

155
00:15:34,487 --> 00:15:35,697
- Of course, man!
- Yeah right!

156
00:15:36,156 --> 00:15:37,574
He gambled all his Christmas money.

157
00:15:37,574 --> 00:15:39,576
- Obviously.
- You're really something, huh.

158
00:15:40,172 --> 00:15:41,663
You don't have money!

159
00:15:42,245 --> 00:15:44,539
Hey, hey! What’s going on?

160
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:46,332
How’s Grace?

161
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,293
She has lots of cravings.

162
00:15:48,418 --> 00:15:49,544
- She's always hungry.
- That’s normal.

163
00:15:49,544 --> 00:15:50,478
Just like you.

164
00:15:50,503 --> 00:15:51,354
Oh really?

165
00:15:51,379 --> 00:15:52,297
Ouch.

166
00:15:52,297 --> 00:15:55,049
- Too early in the morning.
- You’re already annoying this early!

167
00:15:56,926 --> 00:15:57,929
Jay!

168
00:15:59,888 --> 00:16:02,474
Collect everyone’s contribution
for the food.

169
00:16:10,023 --> 00:16:12,192
Ignored? What’s his problem?

170
00:16:18,764 --> 00:16:20,558
Hey, where’s Ci-N?

171
00:16:20,658 --> 00:16:23,119
He’s not here.
He’s not answering my calls.

172
00:16:23,536 --> 00:16:26,164
Huh? What happened to him?

173
00:16:26,456 --> 00:16:28,500
Should I go to their house later?

174
00:16:29,042 --> 00:16:31,669
But what if his grumpy
brother is there?

175
00:16:36,549 --> 00:16:37,675
Hi, Jay!

176
00:16:48,895 --> 00:16:50,271
Damn!

177
00:16:50,605 --> 00:16:52,148
What happened to your lip, bro?

178
00:16:52,148 --> 00:16:53,267
Did you get into a fight?

179
00:16:53,566 --> 00:16:55,318
Looks like your lips
saw some action, Keif.

180
00:16:55,318 --> 00:16:56,524
You want some lip balm?

181
00:16:59,524 --> 00:17:00,734
You deserve it.

182
00:17:01,574 --> 00:17:02,575
Tss.

183
00:17:02,909 --> 00:17:03,910
Hey, what's up.

184
00:17:05,828 --> 00:17:07,455
- Rory!
- Hey!

185
00:17:12,585 --> 00:17:15,296
If you look at us,
it seems like nothing has changed.

186
00:17:15,296 --> 00:17:16,339
Hey, that didn’t hit!

187
00:17:16,339 --> 00:17:18,049
Throw it!

188
00:17:27,850 --> 00:17:30,186
Asshole! Hey asshole!

189
00:17:32,605 --> 00:17:33,642
Fuck!

190
00:17:34,941 --> 00:17:36,024
Chill with that.

191
00:17:41,906 --> 00:17:44,909
But the truth is,
a lot has already changed.

192
00:17:47,203 --> 00:17:48,997
- Hey, bro.
- Ah!

193
00:17:49,956 --> 00:17:51,416
Settle down, settle down.

194
00:17:55,327 --> 00:17:56,704
Welcome back, class!

195
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:05,638
We’ve already started
planning your retreat.

196
00:18:05,972 --> 00:18:07,432
We’re included in that, Sir?

197
00:18:08,224 --> 00:18:12,312
All students join the retreat
before graduating.

198
00:18:12,312 --> 00:18:14,814
For real?
So we’re actually graduating?

199
00:18:17,442 --> 00:18:19,527
All I can say is,

200
00:18:19,527 --> 00:18:21,548
there will be lots of activities
during the retreat.

201
00:18:22,572 --> 00:18:23,656
When is it, Sir?

202
00:18:23,656 --> 00:18:27,535
No definite date yet,
but earlier than the usual retreat.

203
00:18:27,535 --> 00:18:30,622
It’s just a bit tricky because
of the post-final exams.

204
00:18:33,458 --> 00:18:35,251
What’s the post-final exams?

205
00:18:35,752 --> 00:18:37,545
There’s a fifth exam.

206
00:18:37,754 --> 00:18:40,340
And that determines whether
a student passes or not.

207
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:41,142
Huh?

208
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:42,502
Why is there even a fifth exam?

209
00:18:42,925 --> 00:18:46,095
So if a student doesn’t pass,
they won’t graduate?

210
00:18:48,056 --> 00:18:50,391
Don’t worry Jay, I got you.

211
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:51,649
You will graduate.

212
00:19:01,778 --> 00:19:03,738
Food, food, food!

213
00:19:04,322 --> 00:19:06,282
That's all?

214
00:19:06,449 --> 00:19:07,992
That’s all we have left.

215
00:19:08,242 --> 00:19:09,844
You guys still haven’t
pitched in for the groceries.

216
00:19:09,869 --> 00:19:11,429
- True!
- You’re really something, huh!

217
00:19:11,454 --> 00:19:12,597
Alright, alright.

218
00:19:12,622 --> 00:19:15,571
Wow, you're quick to dodge
when it's time to chip in!

219
00:19:16,209 --> 00:19:17,085
Do you hear anything?

220
00:19:17,085 --> 00:19:18,252
One at a time!

221
00:19:21,272 --> 00:19:22,132
Fine, here.

222
00:19:22,157 --> 00:19:23,493
- Let's split it.
- Ah!

223
00:19:24,759 --> 00:19:25,760
Plate.

224
00:19:28,304 --> 00:19:29,415
Dish.

225
00:19:29,681 --> 00:19:30,712
Rice.

226
00:19:31,808 --> 00:19:32,821
More.

227
00:19:36,754 --> 00:19:37,755
Just eat it already.

228
00:19:43,778 --> 00:19:44,987
Move aside.

229
00:19:45,363 --> 00:19:46,781
And if I don’t want to?

230
00:19:52,704 --> 00:19:55,790
Do you want me to tell them what
we did last New Year’s Eve?

231
00:19:57,542 --> 00:19:58,835
What do you want?

232
00:19:59,961 --> 00:20:00,962
Nothing.

233
00:20:00,962 --> 00:20:02,255
You just look cute when you eat.

234
00:20:02,255 --> 00:20:03,548
Is it bad to watch?

235
00:20:04,257 --> 00:20:05,675
Yes! Go away!

236
00:20:07,677 --> 00:20:08,845
Bro, let's share.

237
00:20:09,345 --> 00:20:10,513
All of that is yours?

238
00:20:13,433 --> 00:20:14,600
Is there a problem, Jay?

239
00:20:16,811 --> 00:20:19,647
Ah nothing, he’s just teasing me.

240
00:20:19,981 --> 00:20:21,010
You sure?

241
00:20:31,033 --> 00:20:33,661
Remember, you are mine.

242
00:20:39,292 --> 00:20:40,126
Jay!

243
00:20:40,126 --> 00:20:41,419
No one follow me!

244
00:20:41,419 --> 00:20:42,879
No one is following you.

245
00:20:58,102 --> 00:21:00,313
There, nice!

246
00:21:01,314 --> 00:21:02,732
So refreshing!

247
00:21:03,608 --> 00:21:07,445
I'm sure nobody will bother me here.

248
00:21:08,988 --> 00:21:10,406
Let me call that brat.

249
00:21:22,126 --> 00:21:23,503
He won’t answer.

250
00:21:27,307 --> 00:21:28,490
Ugh!

251
00:21:29,192 --> 00:21:30,193
Fuck!

252
00:21:30,218 --> 00:21:31,260
Who’s that?

253
00:21:32,845 --> 00:21:35,056
Oh, Edrix!

254
00:21:35,681 --> 00:21:37,391
I thought it was someone else!

255
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,893
What are you doing here?

256
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:47,109
Sorry.

257
00:21:47,777 --> 00:21:49,237
I just couldn’t help it.

258
00:21:52,824 --> 00:21:53,991
Do you have a problem?

259
00:21:57,161 --> 00:21:58,371
I’m mad at myself!

260
00:21:59,997 --> 00:22:01,082
I'm such a coward!

261
00:22:03,543 --> 00:22:04,560
Why?

262
00:22:06,546 --> 00:22:08,923
Unrequited love is just
so damn hard!

263
00:22:09,090 --> 00:22:10,466
I can’t even tell her…

264
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:12,718
or show her.

265
00:22:16,013 --> 00:22:17,557
Yeah, that’s really hard.

266
00:22:18,683 --> 00:22:20,768
But at least you’re sure.

267
00:22:21,352 --> 00:22:22,687
It’s only one person.

268
00:22:23,104 --> 00:22:26,399
It's harder when you're stuck
between two.

269
00:22:30,194 --> 00:22:31,863
But who is it anyway?

270
00:22:37,785 --> 00:22:40,454
Wow, she’s pretty!

271
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:42,373
Freya really is pretty.

272
00:22:42,874 --> 00:22:45,543
Yeah, she’s really—WHAT?

273
00:22:47,753 --> 00:22:48,838
That's Freya?

274
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:53,776
F-Freya is the one
you’re talking about?

275
00:22:53,801 --> 00:22:54,819
Yeah.

276
00:22:54,844 --> 00:22:56,037
It's been a long time Jay.

277
00:22:57,638 --> 00:23:00,433
Wow, what a revelation.

278
00:23:01,434 --> 00:23:02,560
But...

279
00:23:03,269 --> 00:23:04,854
let’s keep this between us, okay?

280
00:23:05,980 --> 00:23:07,045
Promise?

281
00:23:19,076 --> 00:23:20,328
You don’t have food?

282
00:23:21,913 --> 00:23:22,496
That’s food?

283
00:23:22,580 --> 00:23:25,141
Yeah, we were eating downstairs.

284
00:23:25,166 --> 00:23:26,717
And you’re here being dramatic.

285
00:23:37,970 --> 00:23:38,779
Whose is this?

286
00:23:38,804 --> 00:23:41,390
- Auntie, I’m really starving promise.
- Looks like it.

287
00:23:41,557 --> 00:23:43,184
Don’t worry, there’s another box there.

288
00:23:43,184 --> 00:23:44,518
All of that is for you.

289
00:23:44,810 --> 00:23:45,853
We have a visitor?

290
00:23:46,312 --> 00:23:49,023
Relax, there’s more in the kitchen.

291
00:23:49,857 --> 00:23:51,108
- This tastes so good, Auntie.
- Good?

292
00:23:51,359 --> 00:23:52,373
Ci-N?

293
00:23:55,738 --> 00:23:56,781
You idiot!

294
00:23:56,948 --> 00:23:58,201
What happened to you?

295
00:23:58,616 --> 00:24:01,077
Do you know how
worried I was, you brat?!

296
00:24:01,285 --> 00:24:02,119
Really?

297
00:24:02,119 --> 00:24:03,310
You were concerned about me?

298
00:24:03,496 --> 00:24:05,831
Wow, you’re so sweet, Jay.

299
00:24:06,123 --> 00:24:07,500
Don’t be like that, Jay-jay!

300
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:08,501
Sorry, Auntie.

301
00:24:08,834 --> 00:24:10,336
This kid didn't attend school today.

302
00:24:12,088 --> 00:24:14,548
I’ll leave you two to catch up.

303
00:24:14,715 --> 00:24:16,092
I’ll prepare dinner.

304
00:24:16,133 --> 00:24:17,343
Thank you, Auntie.

305
00:24:20,972 --> 00:24:22,306
You've got some nerve!

306
00:24:22,348 --> 00:24:23,516
Enjoying the food too much, huh?

307
00:24:23,516 --> 00:24:24,475
Why weren’t you in class?

308
00:24:24,517 --> 00:24:25,366
It hurts, Jay!

309
00:24:25,391 --> 00:24:26,810
- Oh really!
- I’ll tell Auntie!

310
00:24:27,186 --> 00:24:28,451
What happened to you?

311
00:24:32,984 --> 00:24:34,026
What’s the problem?

312
00:24:36,237 --> 00:24:37,240
Because…

313
00:24:38,114 --> 00:24:39,532
my brother locked me up.

314
00:24:40,574 --> 00:24:41,584
He said...

315
00:24:42,034 --> 00:24:44,954
he’s sending me to London
because I keep on causing trouble.

316
00:24:45,246 --> 00:24:47,331
Said I’m wasting my potential.

317
00:24:48,082 --> 00:24:49,667
Of course
I wasn’t going to allow that.

318
00:24:49,667 --> 00:24:52,211
So yeah,
he locked me in my room.

319
00:24:54,171 --> 00:24:55,673
I was worried about you.

320
00:24:57,133 --> 00:24:57,800
Sorry…

321
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,677
He confiscated my gadgets,

322
00:24:59,677 --> 00:25:00,803
I couldn’t message you.

323
00:25:01,262 --> 00:25:02,680
Is that all he did?

324
00:25:03,014 --> 00:25:03,931
He didn't hit you?

325
00:25:03,931 --> 00:25:04,949
No!

326
00:25:04,974 --> 00:25:05,850
You know why?

327
00:25:05,850 --> 00:25:06,308
Why?

328
00:25:06,308 --> 00:25:07,601
Because I ran away.

329
00:25:08,394 --> 00:25:09,895
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

330
00:25:10,396 --> 00:25:13,274
He said if I won’t listen,
I should just leave.

331
00:25:13,983 --> 00:25:15,609
Where would you go?

332
00:25:15,776 --> 00:25:16,777
Here. With you!

333
00:25:16,986 --> 00:25:18,879
That’s not allowed, are you crazy?!

334
00:25:18,904 --> 00:25:20,698
Why not?
Angelo said it was okay.

335
00:25:20,698 --> 00:25:21,949
What Angelo?

336
00:25:22,033 --> 00:25:22,867
You made that up!

337
00:25:22,867 --> 00:25:24,827
Right Angelo, it’s okay?

338
00:25:25,119 --> 00:25:26,287
Yes, that’s true.

339
00:25:26,996 --> 00:25:28,789
Oh—see?

340
00:25:29,957 --> 00:25:31,542
That hurts!

341
00:25:39,759 --> 00:25:41,010
My new home.

342
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:45,473
Won’t they look for you?

343
00:25:45,681 --> 00:25:47,141
No, Mom knows.

344
00:25:47,141 --> 00:25:48,217
I told her.

345
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:49,351
Wow.

346
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:51,604
Of all the people who left home, you're
the only one who asked for permission.

347
00:25:51,604 --> 00:25:52,288
Amazing.

348
00:25:52,313 --> 00:25:53,981
Of course—
so Mom knows where I’m going.

349
00:25:56,650 --> 00:25:58,123
Where are you even going to sleep?

350
00:25:58,486 --> 00:25:59,695
Angelo said in your room.

351
00:26:00,029 --> 00:26:01,197
My room?

352
00:26:02,364 --> 00:26:03,741
- Do you want some?
- Yeah.

353
00:26:04,366 --> 00:26:06,077
Race you to your room!

354
00:26:06,077 --> 00:26:08,829
Idiot! No eating there!

355
00:26:08,829 --> 00:26:09,830
Hey!

356
00:26:09,914 --> 00:26:10,920
Ci-N!

357
00:26:13,042 --> 00:26:15,795
[Ci-N singing]

358
00:26:23,677 --> 00:26:25,054
Ci-N!

359
00:26:39,985 --> 00:26:42,238
Good morning.

360
00:26:44,365 --> 00:26:47,284
Get up!
Your pillow is soaked with your drool.

361
00:26:59,004 --> 00:26:59,922
Ci-N, you're so noisy!

362
00:26:59,922 --> 00:27:01,173
So early in the morning!

363
00:27:09,849 --> 00:27:10,558
I'll go ahead, Jay.

364
00:27:10,558 --> 00:27:11,642
Going downstairs to eat.

365
00:27:16,939 --> 00:27:19,692
Wow, feel at home.

366
00:27:30,202 --> 00:27:31,217
Ouch.

367
00:27:51,390 --> 00:27:53,017
Did Aries do something to you?

368
00:27:56,770 --> 00:27:58,898
What? What did he do?

369
00:28:03,819 --> 00:28:04,935
Let’s go.

370
00:28:04,987 --> 00:28:06,006
Huh?

371
00:28:19,126 --> 00:28:22,296
Ci, wait—talk to me.

372
00:28:22,838 --> 00:28:24,882
What did Aries do to you?

373
00:28:25,883 --> 00:28:26,951
Is it true, Jay?

374
00:28:27,259 --> 00:28:28,474
You’re leaving Section E?

375
00:28:30,221 --> 00:28:31,764
Did Aries tell you that?

376
00:28:32,723 --> 00:28:36,352
He said I should stay away
from you because you’re leaving.

377
00:28:37,728 --> 00:28:39,538
No, don’t stay away from me.

378
00:28:39,563 --> 00:28:41,523
- Crazy.
- Don’t listen to him.

379
00:28:42,024 --> 00:28:43,108
Who said that?

380
00:28:43,683 --> 00:28:45,143
Who said you'll leave Section E?

381
00:28:47,947 --> 00:28:48,756
Who's fighting?

382
00:28:48,781 --> 00:28:50,157
Is there a cockfight?

383
00:28:50,241 --> 00:28:52,409
Jay, you’re leaving Section E?

384
00:28:53,035 --> 00:28:54,511
No!

385
00:28:54,536 --> 00:28:56,205
But that’s what he said!

386
00:28:56,413 --> 00:28:58,499
Why would he say that?

387
00:28:58,791 --> 00:29:00,459
You don’t want to be with
us anymore, Jay?

388
00:29:00,501 --> 00:29:02,753
We can still tolerate your sour attitude.

389
00:29:02,836 --> 00:29:05,005
I thought we were solid Section E.

390
00:29:05,172 --> 00:29:07,424
- Ouch!
- Yeah.

391
00:29:07,633 --> 00:29:11,428
We thought nothing could break us.

392
00:29:11,637 --> 00:29:13,138
- Exactly.
- So dramatic!

393
00:29:13,138 --> 00:29:14,323
It’s not like that!

394
00:29:14,348 --> 00:29:15,357
Was it Aries?!

395
00:29:16,100 --> 00:29:17,685
Keifer, stop!

396
00:29:17,685 --> 00:29:20,396
Jay, don’t leave!
Stay in Section E!

397
00:29:20,396 --> 00:29:22,189
- Don’t leave!
- Ci, enough!

398
00:29:22,189 --> 00:29:23,707
- I don’t care!
- Jay, please don’t!!

399
00:29:23,732 --> 00:29:25,042
What is happening here?!

400
00:29:25,067 --> 00:29:26,819
Jay-jay is leaving Section E!

401
00:29:26,986 --> 00:29:28,112
- Stop!
- Jay, please!

402
00:29:28,112 --> 00:29:29,129
Is that true?

403
00:29:29,154 --> 00:29:29,905
I’m not!

404
00:29:29,905 --> 00:29:31,740
Look—I’ll explain later!

405
00:29:31,740 --> 00:29:34,535
Go to Keifer first,
he might go after Aries! Hurry!

406
00:29:34,868 --> 00:29:36,704
- Ci, no one's leaving!
- Jay please please!

407
00:29:36,704 --> 00:29:37,871
I’m not leaving!

408
00:29:39,415 --> 00:29:40,624
- So dramatic!
- Really?

409
00:29:40,865 --> 00:29:42,784
Yes! That's what I've been saying!

410
00:29:43,002 --> 00:29:44,211
Aries told me to choose:

411
00:29:44,211 --> 00:29:45,462
Either I leave Section E,

412
00:29:45,462 --> 00:29:47,298
or he won't give me
my Dad's number.

413
00:29:47,298 --> 00:29:50,009
But I chose you guys, okay?!
Happy now?!

414
00:29:50,384 --> 00:29:52,511
Let's go, we need to follow Keifer!

415
00:29:52,511 --> 00:29:53,554
Hurry!

416
00:29:53,595 --> 00:29:55,681
- Let’s go!
- I don’t want to! Why?

417
00:29:55,681 --> 00:29:57,349
Are you paying me for this?
I don't want to!

418
00:30:01,061 --> 00:30:02,107
Get up!

419
00:30:12,865 --> 00:30:13,881
Come here.

420
00:30:31,925 --> 00:30:33,385
Is that it, huh?!

421
00:30:40,309 --> 00:30:41,602
Let's go, quickly!

422
00:30:44,938 --> 00:30:46,690
What?
Let's finish this here now!

423
00:30:46,690 --> 00:30:47,608
Okay, let's end it here.

424
00:30:47,608 --> 00:30:48,484
Can someone stop them?!

425
00:30:48,484 --> 00:30:51,111
Enough!
Stop it already!

426
00:30:51,362 --> 00:30:54,698
I guess the rumors are true,
it's really a mess here.

427
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:57,534
Can those losers get out of here already?

428
00:30:57,534 --> 00:30:58,202
Especially you!

429
00:30:58,243 --> 00:31:00,871
Enough!
Don't you dare speak to Jay-jay like that!

430
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:02,748
Jay-jay, you need to leave.

431
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:05,013
Things are getting out of
control because of you.

432
00:31:08,754 --> 00:31:09,974
As if.

433
00:31:10,714 --> 00:31:12,257
Stop it already, let's go.

434
00:31:12,674 --> 00:31:14,134
Not until you swear!

435
00:31:14,301 --> 00:31:16,678
Swear in front of Aries,
you'll never leave us!

436
00:31:18,639 --> 00:31:19,848
Now!

437
00:31:24,396 --> 00:31:25,397
Sorry.

438
00:31:33,612 --> 00:31:34,947
I'm sorry, Aries.

439
00:31:37,324 --> 00:31:39,660
I've said this before,
and I'll say it again.

440
00:31:41,161 --> 00:31:42,830
I'm not leaving Section E.

441
00:31:47,584 --> 00:31:48,710
Yes!

442
00:31:48,794 --> 00:31:50,318
Won’t karma get you for that?

443
00:31:50,587 --> 00:31:52,005
That's your decision.

444
00:31:52,005 --> 00:31:54,007
I hope you won't regret it.

445
00:31:55,092 --> 00:31:57,386
You just lost your chance to
be with your father.

446
00:31:59,596 --> 00:32:00,806
So stupid!

447
00:32:02,933 --> 00:32:05,060
That's what you used to blackmail Jay-jay?

448
00:32:07,771 --> 00:32:09,273
Are you forgetting who I am?

449
00:32:09,565 --> 00:32:11,066
I always get what I want.

450
00:32:12,317 --> 00:32:13,365
Tss.

451
00:32:16,363 --> 00:32:16,989
Don't worry, Jay.

452
00:32:16,989 --> 00:32:19,366
I promise I'm gonna
connect you to your father.

453
00:32:49,146 --> 00:32:51,064
How did you know I was here?

454
00:32:51,655 --> 00:32:55,117
Uhh, Edrix said you're hanging out
here to get some air.

455
00:32:57,863 --> 00:33:00,657
It hasn't even been a week of classes,
yet you got into a fight already.

456
00:33:05,954 --> 00:33:07,122
My hands hurt.

457
00:33:08,081 --> 00:33:09,249
Do it for me.

458
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:19,776
Ouch!

459
00:33:19,801 --> 00:33:21,011
Be gentle!

460
00:33:21,762 --> 00:33:24,389
Who told you to get into a fight then?

461
00:33:24,848 --> 00:33:26,183
Always losing your temper.

462
00:33:32,523 --> 00:33:33,549
I'm sorry.

463
00:33:36,151 --> 00:33:39,530
Wow!
You're getting good at apologizing, huh.

464
00:33:39,821 --> 00:33:40,739
"I'm sorry".
Say it one more time.

465
00:33:40,739 --> 00:33:42,324
One more, come on.
One more time.

466
00:33:42,324 --> 00:33:43,617
Stop making fun of me.

467
00:33:43,742 --> 00:33:45,077
I only apologize to you.

468
00:33:45,994 --> 00:33:47,162
Why just me?

469
00:33:47,162 --> 00:33:49,998
I'm sure you've got a long list of people
you need to apologize to.

470
00:33:49,998 --> 00:33:51,917
Who's first?
Aries, and then—

471
00:33:51,917 --> 00:33:53,043
I don't care.

472
00:33:53,377 --> 00:33:55,295
I don't have feelings for any of them.

473
00:33:56,171 --> 00:33:57,256
Only for you.

474
00:34:10,811 --> 00:34:11,893
Whatever!

475
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:16,858
Please stay.

476
00:34:25,951 --> 00:34:27,703
Please stay.

477
00:34:28,078 --> 00:34:29,096
Keifer…

478
00:34:37,087 --> 00:34:38,755
I'm not giving up on you, Jay.

479
00:34:42,509 --> 00:34:44,094
I'll fight for you.

480
00:34:57,899 --> 00:34:59,359
What kind of dream was that?

481
00:35:00,444 --> 00:35:04,406
That didn't happen,
but it felt so real.

482
00:35:05,907 --> 00:35:08,452
Enough, Jay-jay!

483
00:35:14,449 --> 00:35:16,993
Good morning, Jay! See you.

484
00:35:27,387 --> 00:35:28,416
Ci-N?

485
00:35:44,696 --> 00:35:45,881
I went ahead, Jay!

486
00:35:45,906 --> 00:35:48,283
You’re impossible to wake,
you just kept on groaning.

487
00:35:49,326 --> 00:35:50,369
Shit!

488
00:35:53,538 --> 00:35:55,499
That brat's really gonna get
it from me later.

489
00:35:57,376 --> 00:35:59,086
He actually left me?

490
00:35:59,086 --> 00:36:01,104
And even brought my bike with him!

491
00:36:04,338 --> 00:36:06,385
- What?
- Looks like you're late too.

492
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:09,179
I woke up late,
how about you?

493
00:36:09,346 --> 00:36:10,806
I woke up late, too.

494
00:36:11,556 --> 00:36:12,766
Okay, let's go.

495
00:36:16,228 --> 00:36:17,245
What’s with you?

496
00:36:17,270 --> 00:36:18,271
Don’t look back.

497
00:36:18,438 --> 00:36:20,065
- Why?
- Someone's following us.

498
00:36:21,233 --> 00:36:23,527
Wait, don't look.

499
00:36:24,326 --> 00:36:25,355
What?

500
00:36:28,281 --> 00:36:29,366
Call Keifer.

501
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:30,707
Huh?

502
00:36:31,952 --> 00:36:32,980
Quickly.

503
00:36:33,203 --> 00:36:34,215
Wait, wait.

504
00:36:42,671 --> 00:36:44,047
There's the girl.

505
00:36:44,047 --> 00:36:45,257
Jay, run!

506
00:36:46,299 --> 00:36:47,192
Hey!

507
00:36:47,217 --> 00:36:49,594
Jay-jay, I told you to leave,
why are you still here?

508
00:36:50,512 --> 00:36:51,596
Jay, leave!

509
00:36:53,682 --> 00:36:54,766
The girl!

510
00:36:57,853 --> 00:36:59,438
I won't leave you alone here!

511
00:37:04,526 --> 00:37:06,111
Go!

512
00:37:09,197 --> 00:37:10,157
Are you okay?

513
00:37:10,157 --> 00:37:12,033
I'm good, are you okay?

514
00:37:13,410 --> 00:37:14,745
What was that?!

515
00:37:18,749 --> 00:37:20,709
You thought you won already?

516
00:37:20,709 --> 00:37:22,176
That's just a hint of what's about to come.

517
00:37:22,377 --> 00:37:23,503
What do you need from us?

518
00:37:24,212 --> 00:37:25,380
Her.

519
00:37:26,006 --> 00:37:27,899
We know she's Keifer's girlfriend.

520
00:37:27,924 --> 00:37:30,385
Huh?! He's not my boyfriend!

521
00:37:30,385 --> 00:37:32,471
He said it so himself that
we're not in a relationship!

522
00:37:33,013 --> 00:37:34,848
Do you think we'll believe you?

523
00:37:35,932 --> 00:37:38,268
Jay, we need to escape them.

524
00:37:38,643 --> 00:37:39,327
How?

525
00:37:39,352 --> 00:37:42,689
Just surrender Keifer's girlfriend
to us so it's over with.

526
00:37:42,898 --> 00:37:43,899
This guy's annoying.

527
00:37:43,899 --> 00:37:46,359
Insist it all you want,
I'm not his girlfriend!

528
00:37:47,569 --> 00:37:50,197
And it'll be a bigger mess
if I give her to you.

529
00:37:53,033 --> 00:37:54,097
Jay!

530
00:38:06,463 --> 00:38:08,048
We’ll go ahead.

531
00:38:21,144 --> 00:38:22,316
Where are you?

532
00:38:23,021 --> 00:38:25,398
Why do I feel like something is wrong?

533
00:38:41,328 --> 00:38:43,199
Were you able to contact her?

534
00:38:52,465 --> 00:38:54,553
You don't have to hide it from me.

535
00:38:54,845 --> 00:38:55,971
I already know.

536
00:38:56,429 --> 00:38:58,431
I'm saying this so it's clear…

537
00:38:58,932 --> 00:39:00,183
I'm not backing down.

538
00:39:00,934 --> 00:39:02,853
Even if we're engaged already?

539
00:39:03,228 --> 00:39:04,521
I don't care.

540
00:39:04,813 --> 00:39:06,398
Let Jay-jay decide.

541
00:39:06,773 --> 00:39:08,660
I'll only stop when she tells me to.

542
00:39:19,244 --> 00:39:21,496
Why is Jay-jay still not here?

543
00:39:22,622 --> 00:39:24,124
Do you know where she is?

544
00:39:24,666 --> 00:39:25,559
No.

545
00:39:25,584 --> 00:39:27,043
Keifer!

546
00:39:27,502 --> 00:39:29,713
The tracker shows Jay-jay
is in the hospital.

547
00:39:30,922 --> 00:39:31,923
What?!

548
00:39:37,137 --> 00:39:38,471
Drix, go!

549
00:39:40,390 --> 00:39:41,600
What?!

550
00:39:42,017 --> 00:39:44,436
Boys, over here!

551
00:39:52,110 --> 00:39:53,361
Where are you Jay?

552
00:39:53,528 --> 00:39:54,779
I'm going crazy.

553
00:39:56,823 --> 00:39:58,867
Miss, is there a Jasper
Jean Mariano here?

554
00:39:58,867 --> 00:40:00,410
Wait Sir, I'll check.

555
00:40:01,661 --> 00:40:02,954
Faster, Miss!

556
00:40:03,371 --> 00:40:04,347
I don't have time!

557
00:40:04,372 --> 00:40:05,916
Sir, there's no Jasper
Jean Mariano admitted here.

558
00:40:05,916 --> 00:40:07,542
- Huh?
- What time was she admitted?

559
00:40:07,542 --> 00:40:10,420
A while ago, check it again!
Faster!

560
00:40:10,587 --> 00:40:11,504
Sorry Sir, but there's—

561
00:40:11,504 --> 00:40:13,548
Miss, check it again please.

562
00:40:14,716 --> 00:40:16,176
Guys, here!

563
00:40:17,802 --> 00:40:18,824
Jay!

564
00:40:20,746 --> 00:40:21,598
Jay, I’m coming.

565
00:40:21,598 --> 00:40:23,266
Good thing the wound isn't that deep.

566
00:40:23,266 --> 00:40:26,978
You shouldn't be lifting
heavy things for one week.

567
00:40:35,111 --> 00:40:36,571
Where's Jay-jay?

568
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:41,668
She was right there a while ago.

569
00:40:42,443 --> 00:40:44,654
She disappeared all of a sudden,
she was probably shocked by all the blood.

570
00:40:45,288 --> 00:40:46,414
What did you say?

571
00:40:46,748 --> 00:40:47,415
I don't know, bro.

572
00:40:47,415 --> 00:40:50,168
She just started shaking
when she saw me bleeding.

573
00:40:50,460 --> 00:40:52,504
She didn't talk...

574
00:40:53,088 --> 00:40:54,297
she just kept on crying.

575
00:40:54,339 --> 00:40:55,347
Fuck.

576
00:40:55,715 --> 00:40:58,259
Ever since Ram's gang weakened,

577
00:40:58,802 --> 00:41:00,553
everyone popped out of nowhere.

578
00:41:00,553 --> 00:41:02,764
And they all want to get Jay-jay

579
00:41:04,015 --> 00:41:05,767
because she's Keifer's girlfriend.

580
00:41:07,644 --> 00:41:08,691
I don't even know.

581
00:41:08,937 --> 00:41:12,273
I'm just grateful that
David came to help us.

582
00:41:13,233 --> 00:41:15,819
If it wasn't for him,
we wouldn't even reach the hospital.

583
00:41:17,278 --> 00:41:19,072
Rory, your coffee.

584
00:41:24,494 --> 00:41:26,955
Next time, call me.

585
00:41:26,955 --> 00:41:29,040
Don't try to be a fucking hero.

586
00:41:43,388 --> 00:41:44,402
Hello?

587
00:41:45,147 --> 00:41:46,316
How is she?

588
00:41:47,017 --> 00:41:49,227
She looked terrified
when I found them.

589
00:41:49,686 --> 00:41:52,105
With all that blood,
I thought it was her who got stabbed.

590
00:41:52,564 --> 00:41:54,399
But she was just hugging Rory.

591
00:41:54,607 --> 00:41:56,192
Why did this happen?

592
00:41:56,693 --> 00:41:59,904
What stupid shit did Keifer do this time
for Jay-jay to get involved again?

593
00:42:00,572 --> 00:42:03,825
They all want to use
Jay-jay to beat Keifer.

594
00:42:04,242 --> 00:42:05,277
Huh?

595
00:42:05,535 --> 00:42:07,746
Keifer never uses his head!

596
00:42:08,870 --> 00:42:11,926
So, what's your plan?

597
00:42:12,667 --> 00:42:14,002
None yet.

598
00:42:14,002 --> 00:42:18,048
But when I get back,
they better prepare themselves.

599
00:42:30,310 --> 00:42:31,936
Why?

600
00:42:32,062 --> 00:42:34,314
Why didn't I black out?

601
00:42:35,023 --> 00:42:38,943
Why didn't I attack them
like how I did to Cyrus and Ram?

602
00:42:41,529 --> 00:42:44,032
A lot has happened ever since
I wore this uniform.

603
00:42:44,032 --> 00:42:45,950
Stop it!

604
00:42:46,785 --> 00:42:49,996
Stop it!

605
00:42:56,294 --> 00:43:00,673
But among all of them,
this one's the worst.

606
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:09,516
Jay!

607
00:43:16,689 --> 00:43:18,191
Keifer…

608
00:43:19,275 --> 00:43:20,568
No, no.

609
00:43:21,069 --> 00:43:23,905
Don't cry.

610
00:43:23,905 --> 00:43:26,616
I'm here, don't cry.

611
00:43:27,659 --> 00:43:29,370
Please don't cry, I'm here.

612
00:43:37,252 --> 00:43:40,338
Don't cry, it's okay.

613
00:43:40,505 --> 00:43:41,506
I'm here.

614
00:43:41,798 --> 00:43:42,807
Don't cry.

615
00:43:43,383 --> 00:43:45,009
It's okay.

616
00:43:52,767 --> 00:43:54,394
Is this your blood?

617
00:43:54,769 --> 00:43:56,146
Are you hurt?

618
00:43:57,522 --> 00:43:58,612
No.

619
00:44:00,233 --> 00:44:03,111
I thought the same incident
with Ram would happen again.

620
00:44:03,862 --> 00:44:05,534
I was scared.

621
00:44:05,989 --> 00:44:07,907
It's okay, everything's okay.

622
00:44:07,991 --> 00:44:09,159
Everything’s okay.

623
00:44:09,576 --> 00:44:10,660
Stop crying.

624
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:13,054
It's okay.

625
00:44:13,079 --> 00:44:15,498
I saw lots of blood

626
00:44:16,082 --> 00:44:19,878
but I didn't faint nor harm anyone.

627
00:44:20,229 --> 00:44:22,255
And we'll figure out why.

628
00:44:23,798 --> 00:44:27,594
But for now,
let's get you cleaned up.

629
00:44:28,151 --> 00:44:31,598
I know this is wrong because
Yuri's my fiancé already.

630
00:44:34,184 --> 00:44:36,269
But why do I feel this way?

631
00:44:36,936 --> 00:44:38,855
When it comes to Keifer,

632
00:44:39,397 --> 00:44:41,608
my feelings are certain.

633
00:44:55,163 --> 00:44:57,832
Wait, what are you going to do?

634
00:44:58,583 --> 00:45:00,001
You need rest.

635
00:45:00,001 --> 00:45:01,669
Just shut up and let me.

636
00:45:58,559 --> 00:46:02,230
I'm not giving up on you, Jay.

637
00:46:05,608 --> 00:46:07,026
I'll fight for you.

638
00:46:11,322 --> 00:46:12,991
Is this still a dream?

639
00:46:13,700 --> 00:46:15,743
Shit, someone wake me up!

640
00:46:17,036 --> 00:46:18,705
Game on.

641
00:47:22,518 --> 00:47:24,687
Don’t just let them take what’s yours.

642
00:47:24,873 --> 00:47:26,875
Just because they dared
to make a bold move.

643
00:47:30,979 --> 00:47:31,853
Follow your heart.

644
00:47:31,878 --> 00:47:34,492
Don't listen to distractions
and don't give them an inch.

645
00:47:34,517 --> 00:47:35,851
Were you the one who taught them?

646
00:47:36,032 --> 00:47:38,701
Out of all the boys in Section E,
five of us can do Martial Arts.

647
00:47:38,801 --> 00:47:40,751
Six if you include Mayo too.

648
00:47:40,776 --> 00:47:41,704
Oh "kapour"!

649
00:47:41,704 --> 00:47:44,540
- "Kapour!"
- Parkour!

650
00:47:44,540 --> 00:47:45,208
You said "kapour"!

651
00:47:45,208 --> 00:47:46,559
Stupid, it's parkour!

652
00:47:46,584 --> 00:47:47,960
If I'm the stupid one,
then what are you?

653
00:47:47,960 --> 00:47:48,586
Attention-seeker!

654
00:47:48,586 --> 00:47:49,212
Asshole!

655
00:47:49,212 --> 00:47:50,315
Profanity.

656
00:47:53,716 --> 00:47:55,051
I'm jealous.

657
00:47:55,301 --> 00:47:56,886
I can't help it, Jay.

658
00:47:56,886 --> 00:47:59,347
You agreed to be my fiancée.

659
00:48:04,160 --> 00:48:05,578
Fuck, it's because of Jay-jay?!

660
00:48:05,603 --> 00:48:06,720
Wait, no!

661
00:48:06,745 --> 00:48:07,522
It isn't what it looks like!

662
00:48:07,522 --> 00:48:08,815
Kit!

663
00:48:08,815 --> 00:48:10,183
Even blaming Kit!

664
00:48:10,208 --> 00:48:12,127
Stop talking to Jay-jay like that!

665
00:48:12,193 --> 00:48:15,571
Go flirt with everybody in Section E!

666
00:48:16,410 --> 00:48:18,651
You're no different from Ella,
anyway!

